Package restructureit.qualitymeasurement.processors

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractionCalculator
    Calculates the average number of classes from which a class inherits information in a given project.
    CohesionCalculator
    Calculates average cohesion of the project which is the relatedness among methods of a class based upon the parameter list of methods.
    ComplexityCalculator
    Calculates the average count of all the methods defined in a class.
    CompositionCalculator
    Calculates Extent of part-whole relationship, realized by using attributes which simply is the average amount of user defined attributes declared per class.
    CouplingCalculator
    Calculates the average coupling which is the total count of different number of classes that a class is directly related to.
    DesignSizeCalculator
    Calculates the design size of the input project.
    EncapsulationCalculator
    Calculates the ratio of the number of private attributes to the total number of attributes declared in each class.
    HierarchiesCalculator
    Calculates the number of class hierarchies in the input project.
    InheritanceCalculator
    Calculates the average ratio of the number of methods inherited by a class to the total number of methods accessible by member methods of the class.
    LinesOfCodeCalculator
    Calculates the number of lines of code in a given project.
    MessagingCalculator
    Calculates the average count of the number of public methods in a class.
    PolymorphismCalculator
    Calculates the average number of methods that can exhibit polymorphic behaviour if it is overridden by one or more descendant classes.
